            <thetext>Several tests allow selective runs, so that e.g. certain demos in the Demo Browser are skipped or only a given list of test packages is run in the Test Runner. These ignore/include lists are currently specified in the Simulation JavaScript files, which means they cannot be set individually for each simulation in a test run. These settings should be moved to the &#39;browsers&#39; section of the test run configuration and passed to the Simulation as command line options.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>10923</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2009-07-15 18:39:30 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>qxtest.py (r19608) now passes test browser options to the simulation script. Those simulations that use ignore and/or include lists have been modified accordingly: Test Runner, Demo Browser and API. The previously hard coded ignore/include lists are now configured as defaults that can be overwritten by setting the options in the test controller script.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
